sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.Service_Details
FROM Services s
JOIN Customers_and_Services cs ON s.Service_ID = cs.Service_ID
JOIN Customers c ON cs.Customer_ID = c.Customer_ID
LEFT JOIN Customer_Interactions ci ON s.Service_ID = ci.Service_ID
WHERE c.Customer_Details = 'Hardy Kutch'
   OR ci.Status_Code = 'good'
question: Find the name of all the services which either have been used by customer "Hardy Kutch" or have been rated as "good" in one of the customer interactions.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.Service_Details
FROM Services s
WHERE s.Service_ID IN (
    SELECT cas.Service_ID
    FROM Customers_and_Services cas
    JOIN Customers c ON cas.Customer_ID = c.Customer_ID
    WHERE c.Customer_Details = 'Hardy Kutch'
    UNION
    SELECT ci.Service_ID
    FROM Customer_Interactions ci
    WHERE ci.Status_Code = 'good'
)
